[V1]
 I woke up this morning feeling a little down
 Walked down to my back yard took a good look around
 I walked down the hall, heard the telephone ring
 I went into the bathroom and I done my morning thing
 I walked into the kitchen sure was feeling good
 It was my wife's day to cook breakfast, just like I knew she would
 I look in on my children, still asleep in bed
 I had to thank the Lord cause neither one of them was dead

[C]
 Yeah this time, I just thought I had the blues
